Three days left on this first experiment.

For those who say skeptical people won&#39;t listen to any evidence, here is a great way to provide some publicly and prove or disprove that statement.

And if your&#39;re just the type who maintains an open mind, and would like to try to see what works and what doesn&#39;t, here&#39;s an opportunity to participate in a multi-person test.


--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;rasterer&quot; &lt;rasterer@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; I have placed a little something on top of my computer monitor, right in front of me.  It is now 7/10/2010.  I will leave it there 4 days, and remove it Noon Denver time, on Wednesday, 7/14/2010.
&gt; 
&gt; All you have to do is ask your boxes/spirits/aliens/etc, what it is.
&gt; 
&gt; I have taken a picture of it, and posted it to the files section here, so there is no way I can squirm out of the results:
&gt; 
&gt; http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/EVP-ITC/files/RJ/RJ.20100710.1.zip
&gt; 
&gt; Please do not try to open the file before noon Wednesday.  But feel free to download it to your computer beforehand, so you can be sure I won&#39;t change it during, or after, the test.
&gt; 
&gt; Answers anyone reveals after noon Wednesday don&#39;t count. Partial answers (like just the color, or shape, or some emotion vibe) don&#39;t count.  Just tell me what it is.
&gt; 
&gt; Best of Luck. I hope for this to be a regularly occurring experiment, and I hope we all can learn from the results.
